
# Cursor Rules — BuddyNagar

1. Follow PRD strictly.
2. Do not change UI structure.
3. Use Next.js App Router.
4. Use Supabase backend only.
5. Use shadcn/ui components.
6. Avoid over-engineering.
7. Use Tailwind CSS.
8. API via route handlers only.
9. Mobile-first design.
10. TypeScript strict mode.
11. Reuse components.
12. Handle edge cases.
13. Respect RLS.
14. Implement logging.
15. After completing a PRD phase, update `docs/phasewise.md` (packages, migrations, routes, sections, dependencies, and how it sets up later phases) so it stays the living phasewise build log.